                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.115/19.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul General <persName type="from">Hanna</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate General</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Monterey</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-11-17">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 17, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>An American manager of an American company received a demand from Federal
                    military officers to send at once 10,000 Mexican dollars <pb facs="0880" n="764"
                        xml:id="pg_764"/> to the military headquarters. I am most decidedly opposed
                    to pay such forced loans. We should remain neutral. If we pay the Federals, we
                    will be compelled to pay the rebels later on. Is my position right? Please
                    inform me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
